article.headline: TCU 54, Boise St. 52
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Hank Thorns' basket started a 20-2 run in the final 8:50 and he finished it with a 3-pointer and a layup as TCU rallied for a 54-52 victory over Boise State on Saturday. Boise State (10-8, 0-3 Mountain West) led 50-36 when TCU (11-7, 1-2) began to chip away. Kyan Anderson and Amric Fields hit 3-pointers to keep the TCU momentum going. Anderson led the way for the Horned Frogs with 16 points, and Thorns scored 12. Adrick McKinney provided a big boost on defense with three blocked shots. Derrick Marks scored 13 points to lead Boise State and grabbed eight rebounds to pace his team's 40-28 advantage on the glass.
